@page "/"

<PageTitle>Backgammon Instructions</PageTitle>
<div class="instructions-container">
    <h1 class="mt-4 mb-3">How to Play vs the Computer</h1>

    <p>This version lets you play single games of backgammon against the computer.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>You can win a <strong>single game</strong>, a <strong>gammon</strong>, or a <strong>backgammon</strong>.</li>
        <li>The doubling cube is not implemented yet.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Moving Checkers</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Click the checker you want to move.</li>
        <li>For your first checker move, the game will try to use the <strong>leftmost die</strong>.</li>
        <li>If that move is illegal, it will try the other die instead.</li>
        <li>Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>Z</kbd> to undo your last move.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>Click on the dice to swap their order.</p>
</div>
